(a)  which  is  wholly  or  partly  derived  or  obtained  from 
or by means of any prohibited activity carried out by 
any  person  after  the    commencement  of  this  Act;

(b)  which  is  the  income,  earnings  or  assets  wholly  or 
partly  derived  or   obtained  from  or  by  means  of 
any  property referred  to  in  paragraph  (a);

(c)  which  is  wholly  or  partly  derived  or  obtained  from 
or by means of any property referred to in paragraph 
(a) or (b);

(e)  which,  after  the  commencement  of  this  Act,  is  or 
was  used  to    assist  or  facilitate  any  prohibited 
activity;

―proceedings  under  this  Act‖  means  any  proceedings  under 
any provision   of  this  Act,  including  any  prosecution  for  an 
offence under  this  Act;

(c)  any    local    authority    and    any    other    statutory  
authority  established  by,  and  exercising  powers 
vested in it by, any written  law;

(b)  of  any  circumstances  from  which,  if  reasonable 
inquiries  had  been    made,  it  might  have  been 
discovered  that  the property  is  illegal  property;

(i)  any  lineal  descendant  or  spouse  of  any  lineal 
descendant  of  a   person    referred  to  in  paragraph 
(h);

(a)  identify  the  liable  person  to  be  proceeded  against, 
state his address of residence or business, if known, 
and other relevant  particulars,  which  are  known;

(ii)  the  fresh  application  does  not  relate  to  any 
property  which  was  the  subject  matter  of  any 
earlier application against  him;

(e)  has  been  commingled  with  other  property  which 
cannot be  separated  or  divided  without  difficulty; 
or

(a)  any  person  whom  he  reasonably  suspects  to  have 
committed  or  to  be   committing  an  offence  under 
this  Act;

(a)  refuses  any  officer  authorized  to  enter  or  search, 
access to  any  premises,  or  fails  to  submit  to  search 
by a person authorized  to  search  him;

(c)  fails  to  comply  with  any  lawful  demands  of  any 
police  officer  in   the  execution  of  his  duty  under 
this  Act;

(d)  refuses  or  neglects  to  give  any  information  which 
may reasonably  be  required  of  him  and  which  he  has 
it in his power  to  give;

(ii)  identifying  each  property  sent  out  of 
Malaysia  by  him  during  such  period  as 
may be specified in the notice;

(c)  not to deal with, expend or dispose  of any property 
held  by  him   without  the  prior  written  approval  of 
the Public Prosecutor;

(a)  contravene   any   requirement,   direction,   term   or  
other provision   of   the   order   or   of   any   notice  
issued  under subsection  (6);

